 "incline_code": "Slab & Vertical",
 "intro_html": "The Traumpfeiler route, or Pillar of Dreams in English, is one of the best routes in the area and is justifiably very popular. It sits on the Heiliger Geist cliff, or Holy Ghost in English. The route is a mixed sport trad with plenty of bolts but still worth of a standard rack of wires and cams. Expect to have to follow other parties if you don’t start very early. With a 60m rope and some extended quickdraws the route can be reduced to 5 pitches if you are so inclined. Clearly a classic of the area the route also offers stunning views and reasonably serious climbing.",
